description.standard: Young Thug’s So Much Fun marks the return of one of hip-hop’s most original and innovative voices. The project is filled with hits—no one sounding anything like another—but his duet with Gunna, “Hot,” is probably most exemplary of what his presence means for the game at large. Producer Wheezy’s horns announce a king’s procession, headed by Thug and the marquee MC of his Young Stoner Life records, Gunna. For his part, though, Thug attributes any joy the song may bring simply to him sharing his lifestyle. “You should listen to this track if you want to have fun, if you want to turn up with your friends,” he tells Apple Music. “‘Hot’ is special because it is actually what I just said. It’s so much fun and I made it with my bradas.” Listen to “Hot” in the Rap Life playlist, along with the rest of the songs leading the charge in hip-hop culture today, and if you hear something you like, add it to your library.
description.short: Young Thug and Gunna’s “Hot” is what victory sounds like.
